t^4+t^2
q_4(t) = t^4-\frac{6t^2}{7}+\frac{3}{35}
q_2(t)= t^2 -\frac{1}{3}
\alpha , \beta, \gamma
\alpha q_4(t) +\beta q_2(t) +\gamma q_0(t)
\alpha q_4(t) +\beta q_2(t) +\gamma q_0(t)= t^4 +t^2
\alpha,\beta,\gamma.
\alpha q_4(t)+\beta q_2(t)+\gamma q_0(t)=\alpha t^4+\left(\beta-\frac67\alpha\right)t^2+\left(\frac3{35}\alpha-\frac13\beta+\gamma\right),
\alpha=1,\quad\beta-\frac67\alpha=1,\quad\frac3{35}\alpha-\frac13\beta+\gamma=0.
